# Vienna International Airport, Austria (VIE/LOWW)
# by pos-ki

# The map includes detailed austrian border, airspace boudnaries, TMAs,
# approaches and SIDs, as close to the current AIP as possible, through
# some things were tweaked slightly for better playability. The airlines
# were also done to resemble current traffic as close as possible, but
# there are certainly some differences left.

# In real life, the full approaches are rarely used fully, mostly
# utilized in times of high traffic peaks. It is therefore common
# to achieve the necessary spacing by just vectoring the planes
# to the ILS manually. Departures generally stay below arrivals
# until clear for further climb.

# Around the PESAT waypoint, the airspace is artificially expanded to
# allow planes to hold at this waypoint. Additionally, the altitude
# restriction around Vinnna is tweaked appropriately to allow planes
# on the localizers to go through unpenalized. Make sure the planes
# are stable on the localizer before entering the area.

# Several runway configs are included, through due to the relative
# positions of the runways, quite a few of them require coordination
# of arrivals/departures to keep separation between traffic. This is
# currently not really possible to simulate in the game.

# Due to there being several copies of the same runways to allow for
# various combinations of approaches/SIDs, there currently seems to
# be a bug where takeoffs from a runway used for takeoffs and landings
# simultaneously are not timed properly by the game, despite only one
# copy of the runway being active. This then results in aircraft
# rolling while the previous arrival is still slowing down on
# the runway etc.
